(3) $1,000 or more but less than $5,000, imprisonment with or without hard labor for not
more than five years, a fine of not more than $3,000, or both.
(4) Less than $1,000, imprisonment for not more than six months, a fine of not more
than $1,000, or both.
Proposed law further provides for a penalty consisting of imprisonment with or without hard
labor for not more than two years, a fine of not more than $2,000, or both, for an offender
who violates proposed law relative to an amount of less than $1,000 and has two or more
previous convictions for theft involving an amount of less than $1,000.
Proposed law requires the offender to pay full restitution in accordance with present law
(C.Cr.P. Art. 883.2) to the victim and any other person who has suffered a financial loss as
a result of the offense.
(Adds R.S. 14:67.8)
